{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":634,"text":"Let's talk about manias."},{"time":4691,"text":"Let's start with Beatlemania."}]},{"cues":[{"time":6673,"text":"(Recording of crowd roaring)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":8873,"text":"Hysterical teenagers,"},{"time":11000,"text":"crying, screaming, pandemonium."}]},{"cues":[{"time":14195,"text":"(Recording of crowd roaring)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":17488,"text":"Sports mania:"},{"time":19000,"text":"deafening crowds,"},{"time":22000,"text":"all for one idea --\nget the ball in the net."},{"time":26295,"text":"(Recording) Goal!"},{"time":28000,"text":"Okay, religious mania:"},{"time":30000,"text":"there's rapture, there's weeping,"},{"time":33000,"text":"there's visions."},{"time":35000,"text":"Manias can be good."},{"time":37008,"text":"Manias can be alarming."},{"time":40106,"text":"Or manias can be deadly."}]},{"cues":[{"time":42315,"text":"(Recording of crowd cheering)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":46000,"text":"The world has a new mania."},{"time":48000,"text":"A mania for learning English."},{"time":50632,"text":"Listen as Chinese students\npractice their English,"},{"time":54174,"text":"by screaming it:"}]},{"cues":[{"time":56000,"text":"Teacher: ... change my life!"}]},{"cues":[{"time":58120,"text":"Students: I want to change my life!"}]},{"cues":[{"time":60555,"text":"T: I don't want to let my parents down!"}]},{"cues":[{"time":63642,"text":"S: I don't want to let my parents down!"}]},{"cues":[{"time":67000,"text":"T: I don't ever want\nto let my country down!"}]},{"cues":[{"time":70368,"text":"S: I don't ever want\nto let my country down!"}]},{"cues":[{"time":74000,"text":"T: Most importantly...\nS: Most importantly..."}]},{"cues":[{"time":77563,"text":"T: I don't want to let myself down!"}]},{"cues":[{"time":80271,"text":"S: I don't want to let myself down!"}]},{"cues":[{"time":83000,"text":"How many people\nare trying to learn English worldwide?"},{"time":86167,"text":"Two billion of them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":88690,"text":"Students: A t-shirt. A dress."}]},{"cues":[{"time":92827,"text":"Jay Walker: In Latin America,"},{"time":94470,"text":"in India,"},{"time":96144,"text":"in Southeast Asia,"},{"time":97795,"text":"and most of all, in China."},{"time":100571,"text":"If you're a Chinese student,"},{"time":102000,"text":"you start learning English\nin the third grade, by law."},{"time":107444,"text":"That's why this year,"},{"time":109214,"text":"China will become the world's largest\nEnglish-speaking country."}]},{"cues":[{"time":114283,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":116230,"text":"Why English?"},{"time":117572,"text":"In a single word: opportunity."},{"time":119761,"text":"Opportunity for a better life, a job,"},{"time":122587,"text":"to be able to pay for school,\nor put better food on the table."},{"time":126000,"text":"Imagine a student taking\na giant test for three full days."},{"time":130563,"text":"Her score on this one test\nliterally determines her future."},{"time":135040,"text":"She studies 12 hours a day"},{"time":137548,"text":"for three years to prepare."},{"time":140312,"text":"Twenty-five percent of her grade\nis based on English."},{"time":145264,"text":"It's called the gaokao, and 80 million\nhigh school Chinese students"},{"time":149979,"text":"have already taken this grueling test."},{"time":152375,"text":"The intensity to learn English"},{"time":154668,"text":"is almost unimaginable,\nunless you witness it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":158619,"text":"Teacher: Perfect!\nStudents: Perfect!"}]},{"cues":[{"time":160430,"text":"T: Perfect!\nS: Perfect!"}]},{"cues":[{"time":163000,"text":"T: I want to speak perfect English!"}]},{"cues":[{"time":165444,"text":"S: I want to speak perfect English!"}]},{"cues":[{"time":167765,"text":"T: I want to speak ...\nS: I want to speak ..."}]},{"cues":[{"time":170072,"text":"T: ... perfect English!\nS: ... perfect English!"}]},{"cues":[{"time":172842,"text":"T (yelling more loudly):\nI want to change my life!"}]},{"cues":[{"time":176000,"text":"S (yelling more loudly):\nI want to change my life!"}]},{"cues":[{"time":179976,"text":"JW: So is English mania good or bad?"},{"time":183000,"text":"Is English a tsunami,\nwashing away other languages?"},{"time":187333,"text":"Not likely."},{"time":188579,"text":"English is the world's second language."},{"time":191500,"text":"Your native language is your life."},{"time":193595,"text":"But with English you can become\npart of a wider conversation --"},{"time":197555,"text":"a global conversation\nabout global problems,"},{"time":201285,"text":"like climate change or poverty,"},{"time":204000,"text":"or hunger or disease."},{"time":207000,"text":"The world has other universal languages."},{"time":210499,"text":"Mathematics is the language of science."},{"time":213555,"text":"Music is the language of emotions."},{"time":216571,"text":"And now English is becoming\nthe language of problem-solving."},{"time":221000,"text":"Not because America is pushing it,"},{"time":223238,"text":"but because the world is pulling it."},{"time":226865,"text":"So English mania is a turning point."}]},{"cues":[{"time":230123,"text":"Like the harnessing\nof electricity in our cities,"},{"time":232695,"text":"or the fall of the Berlin Wall,"},{"time":235000,"text":"English represents hope"},{"time":237386,"text":"for a better future --"},{"time":239000,"text":"a future where the world\nhas a common language"},{"time":243000,"text":"to solve its common problems."}]},{"cues":[{"time":246038,"text":"Thank you very much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":247222,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}